{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0115fB6Yd63HSrckL1dGL8xh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import Anthropic from '@anthropic-ai/sdk'\n     2→import { createClient } from '@supabase/supabase-js'\n     3→import { buildPersonaPrompt } from '../../lib/persona'\n     4→import { compressAndSaveMemory } from '../../lib/memoryCompression'\n     5→import { checkDailyRateLimit, rateLimitErrorResponse } from '../../lib/rateLimit'\n     6→\n     7→const anthropic = new Anthropic({ apiKey: process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY })\n     8→\n     9→function getAdminClient() {\n    10→  const url = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL\n    11→  const key = process.env.SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY\n    12→  console.log('[checkin] admin client key prefix:', key?.slice(0, 20))\n    13→  console.log('[checkin:client] url present:', !!url, '| service key present:', !!key)\n    14→  return createClient(url, key)\n    15→}\n    16→\n    17→// ── Tool definitions ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    18→\n    19→const PERSONA_VOICE_INSTRUCTION = `PERSONA VOICE — CRITICAL. You must write in the exact voice of the user's persona blend. Examples of how each persona actually sounds:\n    20→\n    21→DRILL_SERGEANT: \"Dentist done. Insurance call, project email, walk — all overdue. Pick one. Go.\" Short sentences. No praise. Imperative. No questions.\n    22→COACH: \"Good momentum on the dentist call. You've got three things stacking up — insurance, project email, walk. Which one moves the needle most right now?\"\n    23→HYPE_PERSON: \"YES! Dentist call knocked out! Now we're cooking. Three more on the list — insurance, project email, walk. Which one are we CRUSHING next?!\"\n    24→THINKING_PARTNER: \"You got the dentist call done — what made that one easier to start? You've got insurance, project email, and your walk still open. What's actually in the way of the next one?\"\n    25→STRATEGIST: \"Dentist: complete. Three open: insurance call, project email, 30min walk. Highest consequence item is insurance. Recommend starting there. Confirm?\"\n    26→EMPATH: \"Really glad you got the dentist call done — that one takes courage. Three things still open. How are you feeling about tackling the next one?\"\n    27→\n    28→If the user's primary persona is drill_sergeant, write like the DRILL_SERGEANT example. Do not soften. Do not add warmth unless coach is in the blend. Commit fully to the voice.`\n    29→\n    30→const TOOL_USE_RULES = `TOOL USE RULES — CRITICAL:\n    31→When the user confirms a time, date, or scheduling decision during conversation, you MUST immediately call the appropriate tool — do not just acknowledge it conversationally. Examples:\n    32→- User says \"let's do 6pm\" → call reschedule_task with due_time = 6pm today\n    33→- User says \"add that to my list\" → call create_task immediately\n    34→- User says \"mark that done\" → call complete_task immediately\n    35→- User says \"push it to tomorrow\" → call reschedule_task with tomorrow's date\n    36→Never say \"I'll add that\" or \"I've scheduled that\" without actually calling the tool. Talk is not action. Use the tool.\n    37→\n    38→TIME CONVERSION — MANDATORY:\n    39→All datetime values in tool calls must be in UTC (ISO 8601). The user's local time and UTC offset are in the context above.\n    40→Convert before calling: user says \"6pm\" → look up their UTC offset → compute UTC time → use that in the tool call.\n    41→WRONG: due_time: \"2026-03-24T18:00:00.000Z\" when user is UTC-5 and says \"6pm\" (that would show as 1pm local)\n    42→RIGHT: due_time: \"2026-03-24T23:00:00.000Z\" (18:00 local + 5 hours = 23:00 UTC)\n    43→\n    44→FINANCE RULES — MANDATORY:\n    45→When the user asks about their finances, bills, spending, or daily budget — always call get_bills, get_daily_number, or log_spend before responding. Never estimate or guess financial figures. Always get live data. Examples:\n    46→- User says \"how much have I spent today?\" → call get_daily_number first\n    47→- User says \"what bills are coming up?\" → call get_bills first\n    48→- User says \"I just spent $50 on coffee\" → call log_spend immediately\n    49→- User says \"can I afford this?\" → call get_daily_number to check remaining budget`\n    50→\n    51→const TOOLS = [\n    52→  {\n    53→    name: 'reschedule_task',\n    54→    description: 'Reschedule a task to a specific date and time. Use this when confirming a task moves to tomorrow or a specific time.',\n    55→    input_schema: {\n    56→      type: 'object',\n    57→      properties: {\n    58→        task_id: { type: 'string', description: 'The task ID to reschedule' },\n    59→        scheduled_for: { type: 'string', description: 'ISO datetime string for when to schedule' },\n    60→        due_time: { type: 'string', description: 'ISO datetime string for the due time, if specified' }\n    61→      },\n    62→      required: ['task_id', 'scheduled_for']\n    63→    }\n    64→  },\n    65→  {\n    66→    name: 'update_task_time',\n    67→    description: 'Update a task due time based on user input during check-in',\n    68→    input_schema: {\n    69→      type: 'object',\n    70→      properties: {\n    71→        task_id: { type: 'string' },\n    72→        due_time: { type: 'string', description: 'ISO datetime string' }\n    73→      },\n    74→      required: ['task_id', 'due_time']\n    75→    }\n    76→  },\n    77→  {\n    78→    name: 'schedule_morning_checkin',\n    79→    description: \"Schedule the morning check-in notification. Call this when telling the user you'll check in at a specific time.\",\n    80→    input_schema: {\n    81→      type: 'object',\n    82→      properties: {\n    83→        checkin_time: { type: 'string', description: 'ISO datetime string for the morning check-in' }\n    84→      },\n    85→      required: ['checkin_time']\n    86→    }\n    87→  },\n    88→  {\n    89→    name: 'complete_task',\n    90→    description: 'Mark a task as complete when the user confirms they finished it during check-in',\n    91→    input_schema: {\n    92→      type: 'object',\n    93→      properties: {\n    94→        task_id: { type: 'string' }\n    95→      },\n    96→      required: ['task_id']\n    97→    }\n    98→  },\n    99→  {\n   100→    name: 'archive_task',\n   101→    description: \"Archive/remove a task when the user says to remove it, delete it, or says they don't need it anymore\",\n   102→    input_schema: {\n   103→      type: 'object',\n   104→      properties: {\n   105→        task_id: { type: 'string' }\n   106→      },\n   107→      required: ['task_id']\n   108→    }\n   109→  },\n   110→  {\n   111→    name: 'create_alarm',\n   112→    description: \"Create an alarm or reminder. Use when you tell the user you'll check back in at a specific time, or when they mention wanting a reminder.\",\n   113→    input_schema: {\n   114→      type: 'object',\n   115→      properties: {\n   116→        alarm_time: { type: 'string', description: 'ISO datetime string' },\n   117→        title: { type: 'string', description: 'Alarm label' },\n   118→        task_id: { type: 'string', description: 'Optional linked task UUID' }\n   119→      },\n   120→      required: ['alarm_time', 'title']\n   121→    }\n   122→  },\n   123→  {\n   124→    name: 'create_task',\n   125→    description: \"Create a new task for the user. Use when the user mentions something they need to do that isn't already on their list.\",\n   126→    input_schema: {\n   127→      type: 'object',\n   128→      properties: {\n   129→        title: { type: 'string', description: 'The task title' },\n   130→        due_time: { type: 'string', description: 'ISO datetime string for the due time (e.g. 2026-03-24T18:00:00.000Z). Combine scheduled_for date with the time the user specified.' },\n   131→        scheduled_for: { type: 'string', description: 'ISO date string for when to schedule it, defaults to today' }\n   132→      },\n   133→      required: ['title']\n   134→    }\n   135→  },\n   136→  {\n   137→    name: 'add_crew_task',\n   138→    description: 'Add a task to a crew member\\'s task list. Use when the user wants to delegate a task to a family or work crew member.',\n   139→    input_schema: {\n   140→      type: 'object',\n   141→      properties: {\n   142→        crew_id: { type: 'string', description: 'The crew ID to add the task to' },\n   143→        assignee_id: { type: 'string', description: 'The UUID of the crew member to assign the task to' },\n   144→        title: { type: 'string', description: 'The task title' },\n   145→        due_date: { type: 'string', description: 'Optional ISO date string for the due date' }\n   146→      },\n   147→      required: ['crew_id', 'assignee_id', 'title']\n   148→    }\n   149→  },\n   150→  {"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016AACCY39huMRvxZN2Eihwg","session_id":"c92e3624-e3e3-45f1-ae19-e176495ae8ad","uuid":"9c1ca33f-8981-4365-8361-e913e494b8ff","timestamp":"2026-03-26T12:15:54.971Z"}
